get theme support "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=================================================================

NAME
----

get theme support - Allows a theme or plugin to get support of a certain [theme

SYNOPSIS
--------

Allows a theme or plugin to get support of a certain [theme
feature](/Theme_Features "Theme Features").

USAGE
-----

` <?php get_theme_support( $feature ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$feature` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Name for the feature being added.
    Default: *None*

Features list:

-   [Sidebar Widgets](/Widgets_API "Widgets API")
-   [Navigation Menus](/Navigation_Menus "Navigation Menus")
-   [Post Formats](/Post_Formats "Post Formats")
-   [Post Thumbnails](/Post_Thumbnails "Post Thumbnails")
-   [Custom Backgrounds](/Custom_Backgrounds "Custom Backgrounds")
-   [Custom Headers](/Custom_Headers "Custom Headers")
-   [Automatic Feed Links](/Automatic_Feed_Links "Automatic Feed Links")
-   [Editor Style](/Editor_Style "Editor Style")

See [Theme Features](/Theme_Features "Theme Features") for more
information.

FEATURE MEANS
-------------

See
[Function\_Reference/add\_theme\_support](/Function_Reference/add_theme_support "Function Reference/add theme support")
for more.

RETURN
------

Returns either:

-   `array()`{style="font-weight:bold;"} - containing the arguments
    passed when support for the feature was registered via
    `add_theme_support( $feature, $arguments )`; OR
-   `true`{style="font-weight:bold;"} *(bool)* - if support for the
    feature was added without arguments
    (`add_theme_support( $feature )`; OR
-   `false`{style="font-weight:bold;"} *(bool)* - if the feature is not
    supported by the current theme.

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_theme_support()` is located in `wp-includes/theme.php`.

